fields.name: Martin D-28
fields.short_description: A legendary dreadnought with rich bass, powerful projection, and classic tonewoods like Sitka spruce and East Indian rosewood. Ideal for professionals and serious enthusiasts.

fields.name: Taylor 214ce
fields.short_description: A Grand Auditorium acoustic-electric with layered rosewood back and sides, solid Sitka spruce top, and Taylorâ€™s ES2 pickup system. Great for versatile playing styles.

fields.name: Yamaha FG800
fields.short_description: Known for its solid spruce top, strong build, and exceptional value. Great for beginners and intermediate players seeking quality on a budget.

fields.name: Fender CD-60S
fields.short_description: A highly affordable dreadnought with a solid spruce top and easy-to-play neck. Perfect for beginners or those needing a reliable backup guitar.

fields.name: Gibson J-45 Standard
fields.short_description: A historic round-shoulder dreadnought, praised for its warm tone and dynamic response. Premium quality with vintage vibe and modern playability.

fields.name: Epiphone Hummingbird Studio
fields.short_description: A budget-friendly version of the classic Gibson Hummingbird. Features a distinctive pickguard, spruce top, and built-in electronics for stage use.

fields.name: Takamine GD30CE
fields.short_description: A stage-ready dreadnought with a solid spruce top, cutaway design, and Takamine TP-4TD preamp system. Great for live performers.

fields.name: Breedlove Discovery Concert CE
fields.short_description: A stylish, eco-friendly acoustic-electric with a slim neck and bright, balanced tone. Great for fingerstyle and light strumming.

fields.name: Seagull S6 Original
fields.short_description: Canadian-made with a pressure-tested cedar top and wild cherry back/sides. Offers rich midrange and great sustain at a mid-tier price.

fields.name: Ibanez AW54CE
fields.short_description: A warm-sounding dreadnought with a solid mahogany top and Ibanez electronics. Perfect for earthy, natural tones and reliable performance.
